<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#D5E6E1"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000080" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Xaviouss</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Hello me friends, tis I yer humble healer.  I be itchin to conqure that there Permafrost keep.  And I be needen to know more about it.  If yer be knowin then I be a listenin.  Ye know what I mean.  Monsters, treasures, where to go, how to stay me alive.  Thanks much friends and me hat goes off to ye.<P>------------------<BR>Xaviouss </FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Epicurus Quickli</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">First please elaborate what your lvl and class is and what kind of group makeup you have? This matters in this dungeon as things get mighty busy mighty fast in the frozen depths of Perma.<P>Epi/Brood<BR>GoH of Test<BR>Healin and Barshin Norath daily <p>[This message has been edited by Epicurus Quickli (edited 08-29-2000).]</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">EQSeriana</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Just this past week my guild Justifiers of Faith had the honor of having their first all guild raid at Perma on the Terris Thule server. I will tell you what I know. The trains here are phenomenal. There is are Ice Giants guarding the front so you will have to travel north along the wall to find the secret entrance (you can enter and exit thru this entrance).<P>The beginning of Perma is a long tunnel with Gobbies stationed along the way. Our group of 12 to 15's were able to pull from this continously with at times being a little overwhelmed and then regaining control.<P>We moved to the left to the flag room. This room is generally a nice room to pull to. Our group of 16 thru 19's were able to keep this room under control quit easily. There are 4 or 5 (blue/yellow to lvl 17 in this room)..some can even be pulled from adjacent hallways during slow times.<P>We tried to take the priest room and it was beyond our limits even tho the gobbies there didn't con any higher or lower than the ones in the flag room. The reason being is gobbies are frightenly aggressive with a good ratio of casters to melee'rs. It's the casters what will bring you to your knees expecially if they are standing back and healing the nasties that are already on you.<P>This dungeon can not be taken quickly. The gobbies may con green and you can take a whole bunch of em at a time, but they nearly always run when on low health and one lost gobby screaming curses at you from inside the dungeon will bring down a rain of uglies such as a sight you may have never seen before. Gate, evac,rezz and a lotta healing needed here.<P>If you come plan to stay awhile.<BR>That is as much as I know so far and I am lucky to know that much.<BR>Great Raid Guys..see you in two weeks for the next<P>Seri<BR>19th Season Monk<BR>Silent Fist Clan<BR>Justifiers of Faith<BR>Terris-Thule<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">taobob</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">We actually conducted a similar raid that I attended with our guild The Lords of the Anchients on The Nameless server. <P>The entranceway contains 5 goblins all grouped together, that are between the levels 15-17. Then as you proceed up the ladder from the entranceway into the tunnel there are 5 more spawn spots all for lower level goblins. <P>Immediately after this is the flagpole room where there are as many as 8 goblins at one time, and some of them are casters of approx level 17-19. <P>I really was unable to venture any further however, as I was stationed with the lower level 12-15 members of my guild, but I can tell you that these goblins all drop decent loot and are good at protecting their friends.<P>------------------<BR>Atreu<BR>Human Monk <BR>12th Season<BR>The Nameless </FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Walil</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial"> Its not to bad. We had a small group go through and camp the priest, arche, and the king. The trick is to have a good enchanter and someone who can snare. It makes the journery a lot safer. We were split about 1/2 low 20's and the other 1/2 lower 30's. <P> You best bet is to go in invis and just movde past those first gobbo's. If you want an adventure than fight your way though step by step. Thats what we have been doing in Sol A and its a blast. </FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Inky Caster</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Well nobody has mentioned the real reason to visit Perma... You see there's this big dragon in the back which drops Phat loot hehehe. Her name is Lady Vox and she is now level 55. Here is a brief strategy on how to take her out. COLD RESIST GEAR! that is necesary. Also Chanters and Clerics need to cast stuns on here once she is below half life because she is a cleric and will attempt to Complete Heal herself. The rest I am not going to explain because anyone who is going to attempt to kill her knows how to take on a big mob.<BR>P.S.-She is a Giant Class Mob so stuns dont work on her, but they will interupt her casting if it  is not resisted.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Faeadari</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Ahhh Permafrost- spent many an hour as a lvl 13-18 wizard in that zone.<P>The zone line is great exp for the low to mid teens- the key being to break the spawn- at 16 a lvl 18 shaman and I were able to break it- then we got trained by careless higher ups.<P>The trains- what tends to happen in this zone is that since it is so undercamped that those in the 20's will pull too much and then start to run.  <P>Now there is some great loot to be had- bard lambiant, shaman totem, and warrior crafted quest items drop here.  There are also nice drops for both wis and int based casters and hybrids (there is a pair of boots in their I covet).<P>Vox is buried deep within this dungeon and is wayyyy to fat to fit through the door- so there is no chance of her popping up on you.<P>Still wondering though- who's idea it was for us to loot gobbies by clicking on their butt crack  <IMG SRC="http://www.eqatlas.com/ubb/smile.gif"><P>Faeadari Freespyrt<BR>High Elf Wizard of the 34th degree<BR>Bloodsong<BR>Lanys<BR></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
</FONT>
